# Summary

Adds repository-level guidance files so Copilot and contributors have consistent, project-aware instructions for backend, frontend, and tests.

# Files added
- .github/copilot-instructions.md — repository-level Copilot guidance (project identity, core stack, multi-tenant rules, backend patterns, data modeling, testing, and “avoid” list).
- .github/instructions/backend.instructions.md — guidance for Python backend files under app/**/*.py (architecture, RBAC, scoping, service-layer rules, schema/model rules, tests).
- .github/instructions/tests.instructions.md — test guidance applied to tests/**/*.py (focus, tenant/location isolation, fixtures).
- .github/instructions/frontend.instructions.md — frontend/template guidance (dark-mode, navigation, context visibility, reusable components).
- AGENTS.md — repository-level agent/assistant mission and execution rules (roadmap alignment, safety rules, testing and output expectations).

# Intent

Centralize repository-level behavioral and implementation guidance so contributors and automated assistants produce changes that align with HN3T_MASTER_PLAN.md and the repo’s multi-tenant, location-aware constraints.

# Next steps
- Convert this PR to Draft (recommended while reviewing wording).
- Review the files for any wording edits.
- Request reviewers and merge when ready.
